headline: Jobs report, Nike, Fed, govt. shutdown: What to Watch Next Week
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews several of the biggest stories to come throughout next week, including September's jobs data due out next Friday, October 3, earnings from companies like Nike (NKE) and Carnival (CCL), the latest commentary from Federal Reserve officials, and a possible government shutdown as US lawmakers continue to negotiate a spending bill. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Star Princess Officially Delivered to Princess Cruises
summary: Star Princess - the second Sphere-Class ship in the Princess Cruises fleet - was officially delivered today during a celebratory handover ceremony at the Fincantieri Shipyard in Monfalcone, Italy. The stunning Star Princess is the 17th ship in the cruise line's dynamic line up of vessels sailing worldwide.
